Amazon S3

CRR (Cross-region replication): enables automatic, asynchronous copying of objects across buckets in different AWS Regions.

Durability: 99.999999999% (11 9's).

Consistency: Strong consistency for all operations (PUTs/DELETEs).

Bucket names rules:

Names must be unique across all of AWS.

Names must be 3 to 63 characters in length.

Names can only contain lowercase letters, numbers and hyphens.

Amazon S3 storage classes (2026):

S3 Standard -> Frequently accessed data.

S3 Standard-IA -> Infrequent access, rapid retrieval.

S3 One Zone-IA -> Cost-effective, single AZ (less durable).

S3 Intelligent-Tiering -> Unknown/changing access patterns (Auto-tiering).

S3 Glacier Instant Retrieval -> Millisecond retrieval for rare access.

S3 Glacier Flexible Retrieval -> Minutes to hours.

S3 Glacier Deep Archive -> Lowest cost, 12-48 hours.

Multipart upload can be used to speed up uploads to S3.

"MFA delete" adds a layer of additional security to prevent accidental deletion.

Amazon S3 objects consist of: Key, Value, Version ID, Metadata.

Object lifecycle management: Automated rules to transfer objects between classes or expire them.

Standard-IA and One Zone-IA both have a minimum storage duration charge of 30 days.

Six advantages of Amazon Cloud (Benefits)

Trade capital expense (CAPEX) for variable expense (OPEX).

Benefit from massive economies of scale.

Stop guessing about capacity.

Increase speed and agility.

Stop spending money running and maintaining data centres.

Go global in minutes.

AWS Compute Optimizer

It helps avoid over/underprovisioning based on utilization data for:

Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) instance types.

Amazon Elastic Block Store (EBS) volumes.

Amazon Elastic Container Service (ECS) services on AWS Fargate.

AWS Lambda functions.

Amazon EBS volumes types

General purpose (gp3 / gp2) (SSD): Balanced price/performance. gp3 is the latest generation.

Provisioned IOPS (io2 / io1) (SSD): Highest performance for IOPS-intensive apps.

Cold HDD (sc1): Lowest cost, throughput-oriented for infrequent data.

Throughput Optimized (st1): Fast throughput for big data/streaming.

Amazon Elastic Load Balancer (ELB)

Distributes incoming traffic across multiple targets (EC2) in multiple Availability Zones.

ELB Health Check monitors instance health.

A listener checks for connection requests using the protocol and port you configure.

Amazon Load Balancers

Application Load Balancers (ALB): Layer 7 (HTTP/HTTPS).

Network Load Balancers (NLB): Layer 4 (TCP/UDP/TLS). Ultra-low latency.

Gateway Load Balancers (GLB): For deploying 3rd party virtual appliances.

Classic Load Balancers (CLB): Legacy, Layer 4 & 7.

AWS Network Access Control List (ACL)

Stateless.

Operates at VPC subnet level.

Supports both Allow and Deny rules.

AWS Security Groups

Stateful firewalls.

Operates on EC2 instance level.

Only Allow rules (no explicit deny).

AWS Internet Gateway

Allows public traffic to access VPC resources.

Attached at the VPC level.

AWS Scalability

Scaling vertically: Increasing instance size (CPU, RAM).

Scaling horizontally: Adding more instances (Auto Scaling).

Amazon Simple Notification Service (SNS)

Pub/Sub messaging. Sends notifications from the cloud.

Supports HTTP/HTTPS, Email, SQS, and SMS.

Integrates loosely-coupled, distributed applications.

Amazon Simple Queue Service (SQS)

Fully managed pull-based message queuing service.

Use case: Decoupling microservices to ensure independence between components.

Ensures persistence of in-flight transactions.

Amazon Simple Email Service (SES)

Scalable service for sending and receiving emails (transactional/marketing).

AWS Inspector

Automated security assessment for EC2 instances and container images for vulnerabilities.

AWS Trusted Advisor

Five categories: Cost optimization, Security, Performance, Service limits, Fault tolerance.

Provides real-time guidance based on AWS best practices.

AWS Health Dashboard

AWS Health Dashboard: (Replaces Personal Health Dashboard) Provides personalized view into performance and availability of AWS services impacting your account.

AWS X-Ray

Helps developers analyze and debug distributed applications (tracing).

AWS Pricing Calculator

(Replaces TCO Calculator) Used to estimate the cost of AWS services for your specific use cases.

Amazon Elastic Block Store (EBS)

Snapshot backups are stored on Amazon S3.

EBS volumes must be in the same AZ as the instances they are attached to.

Use Amazon DLM (Data Lifecycle Manager) to automate snapshots.

Charged for provisioned capacity per month and provisioned IOPS.

Amazon SageMaker

Build, train, and deploy machine learning models at scale.

Amazon Kinesis

For processing or analyzing streaming data in real time (Video, Data, Analytics).

Cloud Computing

On-demand delivery of compute, storage, and databases via the internet.

Benefit from massive economies of scale and increased agility.

AWS CloudFormation

Infrastructure as Code (IaC). Declare resources in templates (JSON/YAML).

Change sets: Preview impacts of stack changes before applying.

AWS Elastic Beanstalk

PaaS for the fastest deployment of web applications; manages scaling and health automatically.

AWS Lambda

Serverless compute. Triggered by S3 events, HTTP requests (API Gateway), or SQS queues.

AWS Well-Architected Framework

Operational excellence

Security

Reliability

Performance efficiency

Cost optimization

Sustainability (Added as the 6th pillar in modern standards)

AWS WAF

Web Application Firewall. Blocks common attack patterns like SQL injection and Cross-site scripting.

AWS Shield

Managed DDoS protection service.

Standard: Free, for common attacks.

Advanced: Paid, for sophisticated attacks and 24/7 access to Response Team.

AWS AD Connector

Redirects directory requests to your on-premise Active Directory.

AWS Simple AD

Standalone Active Directory-compatible service (does not connect to on-premise AD).

Amazon Elastic Kubernetes Service (EKS)

(Renamed) Managed Kubernetes service to run Kubernetes without managing the control plane.

Amazon Elastic Container Service (ECS)

Orchestration for Docker containers on EC2 or Fargate.

Amazon Elastic Container Registry (ECR)

Secure hosting for container images.

Virtual Private Gateway

VPN concentrator on the AWS side of a VPN connection.

VPC peering connection

Routing traffic between VPCs using private IP addresses. Works across accounts and regions.

AWS Site-to-Site VPN

Secure connection between your data center and AWS resources.

AWS App Mesh

Application-level networking for microservices.

AWS support plans

Basic: 24/7 customer service, documentation, 7 core Trusted Advisor checks.

Developer: Business hours email support.

Business: 24/7 phone/chat/email. 1-hour response for Production Down.

Enterprise: Includes TAM (Technical Account Manager). 15-minute response for Business Critical Down.

Amazon IAM

Identity and Access Management.

Free to use. Use Least Privilege and MFA.

Supports Identity Federation (SSO).

Amazon Cognito

User sign-up/sign-in for web and mobile apps.

AWS Organizations

Consolidated billing and policy-based management for multiple accounts.

Volume pricing discounts applied across all linked accounts.

Popular HTTP code

200: Success

300: Redirection

400: Client Error

500: Server Error

AWS CloudTrail

Logs all API calls for auditing and compliance. (Who, what, when).

Amazon CloudWatch

Repository for metrics and logs. Monitoring and Alarms.

Amazon DynamoDB

Managed NoSQL database. Schema-less. Data synced across 3 AZs.

AWS Database SQL type

Amazon RDS, Amazon Aurora, Amazon Redshift.

AWS Device Farm

Test apps on real physical devices in the AWS cloud.

AWS Config

Audits and records resource configurations. Evaluates configurations against desired states.

AWS Shared Responsibility Model

AWS: Security OF the cloud (Infrastructure, Hardware, Managed Services).

Customer: Security IN the cloud (Data, OS patching on EC2, IAM, Encryption).

Amazon RDS

Managed Relational Database Service.

Multi-AZ: Synchronous for High Availability.

Read Replicas: Asynchronous for read scalability.

AWS Auto Scaling

Scaling Policy: Simple, Scheduled, Dynamic, or Predictive.

AWS CloudHSM

Dedicated hardware security module in the cloud for cryptographic keys.

AWS Glacier

Retrieve data via Standard (3-5 hr), Expedited (1-5 min), or Bulk (5-12 hr).

AWS Storage Gateway

File Gateway, Volume Gateway (Stored/Cached), Tape Gateway.

Amazon OpenSearch Service

(Replaces Amazon Elasticsearch Service) For operational analytics, logs, and real-time search.

Amazon Athena

Serverless SQL interogation of data in S3.

Amazon QuickSight

Business intelligence (BI) and dashboards.

Amazon Route 53

Global DNS service.

Policies: Simple, Weighted, Latency, Failover, Geolocation, Geoproximity, Multi-value.

Amazon CloudFront

Content Delivery Network (CDN) using Edge Locations to cache content globally.

Amazon Lightsail

Preconfigured VPS (Virtual Private Servers) with compute, storage, and networking.

Amazon EC2 pricing

On-Demand: No commitment.

Spot: Spare capacity for short-term requirements (Interruptible).

Reserved Instances: 1 or 3 year commitment for discount (Standard, Convertible).

Dedicated Hosts: Physical servers dedicated to you.

AWS Cost Explorer / Anomaly Detection

Cost Explorer: View cost charts and forecasts.

Anomaly Detection: Alerts when unexpected spending is detected.

AWS Artifact

Portal for downloading AWS security and compliance reports (PCI, SOC, ISO).

AWS Snow family

Snowcone: 8-14 TB.

Snowball Edge: Petabyte-scale data migration.

Snowmobile: 100 PB shipping container.

Six Rs strategies for migration

Rehosting (Lift-and-shift)

Replatforming (Lift-tinker-and-shift)

Refactoring (Re-architecting)

Repurchasing (SaaS)

Retaining (Keep on-premise)

Retiring (Decommission)

Notes

Loose Coupling: Components are independent; if one fails, others aren't affected.

VPC Wizard Options: Single Public, Public/Private, Public/Private+VPN, Private+VPN.

Stateful (SG): Automatically allows return traffic.

Stateless (NACL): Requires separate rules for inbound and outbound.

Golden Image: AMI snapshot used for consistent resource creation.

Bootstrapping: Running code (User Data) at instance launch.

Shared Responsibility: Customer patches OS on EC2; AWS patches OS on RDS.

Direct Connect: Dedicated private connection (not over internet).

VPN: Encrypted connection over the public internet.
